# Vite (Laravel)

- Use **Vite** for asset bundling (CSS, JS, React). Laravel’s default is Vite; use `npm run dev` / `npm run build`.
- Entry: `resources/js/app.jsx`; import global CSS from `resources/css/app.css` in the entry.
- In Blade, use `@vite(['resources/css/app.css', 'resources/js/app.jsx'])` in the layout.
- **HMR off by default:** `npm run dev` sets **`LARAVEL_VITE_NO_AUTO_RELOAD=1`** (via **cross-env**) so **`vite.config.js`** sets **`server.hmr: false`** (disables React Fast Refresh) and turns off **`laravel-vite-plugin`** file-watch refresh. Use **`npm run dev:hmr`** for standard Vite HMR.
- Keep **Tailwind and daisyUI** in the main CSS (`@import "tailwindcss";` and daisyUI plugin as per [daisyUI install](https://daisyui.com/docs/install/)).
